wondering how to invest in ETFs?</i>


993
01:29:26.650 --> 01:29:31.490
<i>I'd tell any first-time investor listening</i>

994
01:29:31.530 --> 01:29:33.320
<i>not to do it alone.</i>

995
01:29:33.370 --> 01:29:34.830
<i>Work with an advisor.</i>

996
01:29:35.450 --> 01:29:40.040
<i>Your advisor can invest
in an ETF in your name.</i>


997
01:29:59.020 --> 01:30:02.100
TRANSFERRING FILES

998
01:30:39.220 --> 01:30:41.060
You have a lot of reading to do.

999
01:30:41.100 --> 01:30:43.310
You can draw your own conclusions.

1000
01:30:45.270 --> 01:30:48.690
So what do I do now?

1001
01:30:49.150 --> 01:30:52.240
Until we have enough proof, you stay put.

1002
01:30:53.780 --> 01:30:56.200
I have to get more information?

1003
01:30:57.080 --> 01:31:01.000
You're asking me to go
from witness to double agent.


1004
01:31:30.780 --> 01:31:33.190
How much in total?

1005
01:31:33.240 --> 01:31:35.240
Seems like it's over everywhere.

1006
01:31:35.280 --> 01:31:38.450
It's more than we thought,
but I think we can absorb it.


1007
01:31:41.410 --> 01:31:42.870
How much?

1008
01:31:44.750 --> 01:31:48.170
If we go with scenario A,
to be safe,


1009
01:31:48.210 --> 01:31:51.840
Norbourg should disclose
a sum of about $63 million.


1010
01:31:52.260 --> 01:31:56.430
So we'd have to pay about $21.3 million

1011
01:31:56.470 --> 01:31:58.600
in federal and provincial taxes.

1012
01:31:58.640 --> 01:32:00.010
$21 million?

1013
01:32:01.100 --> 01:32:04.060
Jesus Christ!
At first, Éric said $12 million.


1014
01:32:04.100 --> 01:32:06.890
Luc, you told me $14 million.
Now I'm at $21 million?


1015
01:32:06.940 --> 01:32:09.440
What the fuck?
That's practically double!


1016
01:32:09.480 --> 01:32:11.150
Yeah.

1017
01:32:11.190 --> 01:32:15.280
With that, Vince,
we're buying peace for five years.


1018
01:32:45.890 --> 01:32:47.390
Thank you.

1019
01:33:34.520 --> 01:33:35.900
Listen…

1020
01:33:37.860 --> 01:33:39.650
I asked you here tonight…

1021
01:33:40.910 --> 01:33:43.160
because you're all important players.

1022
01:33:44.660 --> 01:33:46.660
You stayed loyal.

1023
01:33:49.160 --> 01:33:53.420
Look, I'd like to offer everyone
a stake in Norbourg.


1024
01:33:54.130 --> 01:33:58.260
But I don't know how to divide it.

1025
01:33:59.800 --> 01:34:01.760
I don't want any fighting.

1026
01:34:01.800 --> 01:34:03.600
So…

1027
01:34:05.640 --> 01:34:10.730
I've decided to give everyone a fixed sum.

1028
01:34:12.400 --> 01:34:13.770
To thank you.

1029
01:34:15.320 --> 01:34:17.070
For your loyalty.

1030
01:34:27.540 --> 01:34:29.040
Excuse me.

1031
01:35:00.570 --> 01:35:03.450
It's a first draft
of my analysis of the situation.


1032
01:35:04.950 --> 01:35:08.330
I can continue my analysis, but…

1033
01:35:09.290 --> 01:35:11.040
I need certain guarantees.

1034
01:35:12.290 --> 01:35:13.580
We're listening.

1035
01:35:14.210 --> 01:35:17.590
I want full immunity
against any potential legal action.


1036
01:35:18.366 --> 01:35:20.000
I want physical protection,

1037
01:35:20.050 --> 01:35:23.630
'cause I won't make any friends
spilling dirt on Norbourg.


1038
01:35:24.840 --> 01:35:28.720
I want a permanent position
in public service and $1 million.


1039
01:35:29.220 --> 01:35:31.020
Listen, Asselin…

1040
01:35:31.060 --> 01:35:32.730
Those are quite the demands.

1041
01:35:33.140 --> 01:35:35.770
We don't have the authority
to settle that here.


1042
01:35:37.730 --> 01:35:41.940
Well, hurry,
'cause he's burning through the cash.


1043
01:35:43.530 --> 01:35:46.820
He just spent $2.6 million
on an inn in Magog.


1044
01:35:46.860 --> 01:35:49.580
He bought the Grand Café
for $750,000 cash.


1045
01:35:49.620 --> 01:35:51.660
And he's about to buy Chez Parée!

1046
01:35:55.160 --> 01:35:57.460
He wants to give me $900,000.

1047
01:35:57.500 --> 01:35:59.210
He says it's for past services.

1048
01:35:59.250 --> 01:36:02.760
He's doing the same
for Bernier, Davila and Bilodeau!


1049
01:36:05.260 --> 01:36:08.600
He's trying to compromise them
and buy their loyalty.


1050
01:36:08.640 --> 01:36:11.060
So what do I do?
Do I take the check?


1051
01:36:11.100 --> 01:36:13.430
Or I give it to you to deposit?

1052
01:36:13.470 --> 01:36:16.640
Well, we can't tell you what to do.

1053
01:36:17.310 --> 01:36:21.190
Well, that's too bad then,
but I'm not showing my face there again.


1054
01:36:24.280 --> 01:36:28.410
If you choke, the little deal
you're trying to negotiate…


1055
01:36:34.200 --> 01:36:38.290
Was there anyone at the firm before you
who can corroborate your story?


1056
01:36:38.710 --> 01:36:40.170
I don't know.

1057
01:36:41.090 --> 01:36:42.800
Well, think.

1058
01:36:47.430 --> 01:36:49.640
And to help you think, Éric,

1059
01:36:49.680 --> 01:36:53.430
we learned you received
some very generous bonuses in February.


1060
01:36:55.480 --> 01:36:58.980
If you want to take that road,
I can just go to the cops.


1061
01:36:59.020 --> 01:37:02.110
I want compensation.
That's non-negotiable!


1062
01:37:02.860 --> 01:37:06.190
Without me,
you wouldn't know squat about Norbourg.


1063
01:37:20.040 --> 01:37:24.960
I have here a written confirmation
from the IMET


1064
01:37:25.000 --> 01:37:29.720
that nothing in your statements to us
and no documents you've provided


1065
01:37:29.760 --> 01:37:31.840
will be used against you.

1066
01:37:33.350 --> 01:37:36.220
You think I'm gonna negotiate
with a gun to my head?


1067
01:37:36.680 --> 01:37:39.100
No, this isn't a negotiation.

1068
01:37:39.810 --> 01:37:41.650
It's our final offer.

1069
01:37:42.520 --> 01:37:45.110
You don't have to sign it,

1070
01:37:45.150 --> 01:37:49.530
but if I were you,
I'd sign it, and fast.


1071
01:37:50.700 --> 01:37:53.780
You know, we looked into you closely.

1072
01:37:55.120 --> 01:37:56.330
Bullshit!

1073
01:37:56.370 --> 01:37:57.540
Fine.

1074
01:37:58.580 --> 01:38:01.920
If you want, we could look into
the fascinating file


1075
01:38:01.960 --> 01:38:06.750
on your brand-new little castle
on Harfang Street in Beauport,


1076
01:38:06.800 --> 01:38:09.220
paid for in cash on June 7.

1077
01:38:53.760 --> 01:38:56.720
No matter what way I look at it,

1078
01:38:56.760 --> 01:39:01.430
I can't figure out how so much cash
just drops into the company coffers.


1079
01:39:01.480 --> 01:39:05.480
Listen, with Norbourg International,
the Bahamas,


1080
01:39:05.520 --> 01:39:09.690
it's gotten so complex that
only Vincent really knows how it works.


1081
01:39:09.730 --> 01:39:12.490
Well, I have to understand
where the funds come from,


1082
01:39:12.530 --> 01:39:14.570
'cause we can all see how they're spent.

1083
01:39:14.610 --> 01:39:17.740
Private jets,
offices all over the province,


1084
01:39:17.780 --> 01:39:19.120
box seats at the hockey stadium…

1085
01:39:19.160 --> 01:39:23.040
Vincent can't spend like this forever.
We'll hit a wall.


1086
01:39:24.766 --> 01:39:29.300
Has it ever crossed your mind that
maybe Vincent is financing acquisitions


1087
01:39:29.340 --> 01:39:31.670
by dipping into the investment funds?

1088
01:39:31.710 --> 01:39:35.180
Of course not. 
There's no way.

1089
01:39:35.220 --> 01:39:37.100
Norbourg is too scrutinized.

1090
01:39:37.930 --> 01:39:39.810
I don't know, Éric.

1091
01:39:40.680 --> 01:39:42.180
I don't want to believe it,

1092
01:39:42.230 --> 01:39:46.350
but I've got Bernier saying I'll never see
the books at Norbourg International.


1093
01:39:47.480 --> 01:39:49.020
I'll talk to him.

1094
01:39:58.030 --> 01:39:59.530
Don't worry.

1095
01:40:00.160 --> 01:40:03.330
I repeat, the accounts are fine.

1096
01:40:09.540 --> 01:40:12.710
Luc, could I please

1097
01:40:12.760 --> 01:40:17.800
have access to all the accounts
for every branch of Norbourg?


1098
01:40:21.220 --> 01:40:22.720
Jesus Christ!

1099
01:40:26.310 --> 01:40:28.730
I'm VP of compliance.

1100
01:40:28.770 --> 01:40:32.440
So if I want to see the accounts,
you show me the accounts.


1101
01:40:32.480 --> 01:40:33.900
Is that clear?

1102
01:40:36.200 --> 01:40:38.360
Over my dead body.

1103
01:40:56.300 --> 01:41:00.890
Francis, I want access
to the Norbourg International accounts.


1104
01:41:02.430 --> 01:41:03.850
Give him the codes.

1105
01:41:09.560 --> 01:41:11.270
Log me in.

1106
01:41:11.310 --> 01:41:12.690
Log me into the NAI account,

1107
01:41:12.730 --> 01:41:15.490
account 23-01-34-16
at the Bank of Montreal.


1108
01:41:15.530 --> 01:41:16.780
Go.

1109
01:41:25.540 --> 01:41:27.960
Could you give us a moment, Francis?

1110
01:41:38.630 --> 01:41:40.090
OK…

1111
01:41:55.110 --> 01:41:56.860
Jesus…

1112
01:41:58.780 --> 01:42:03.160
The transfers are from the Evolution Fund,
Unicyme and Canadian Equity.


1113
01:42:04.580 --> 01:42:06.740
The money shouldn't be transferred there.

1114
01:42:06.790 --> 01:42:09.660
Investor dollars
should be in trust accounts,


1115
01:42:09.710 --> 01:42:11.920
not at Norbourg International!

1116
01:42:16.550 --> 01:42:17.920
What's this?

1117
01:42:18.510 --> 01:42:23.760
Over $6 million sent to
Vincent Lacroix's account on July 22.


1118
01:42:31.390 --> 01:42:35.820
It's the first $6 million payment
for his voluntary disclosure.


1119
01:42:35.860 --> 01:42:37.400
That's where he got it.

1120
01:42:42.240 --> 01:42:45.700
Asselin, this is fucking crazy!

1121
01:42:48.870 --> 01:42:51.920
We absolutely have to
report this to the Authority.


1122
01:42:53.670 --> 01:42:56.380
Let's go to my office. Come.

1123
01:43:07.220 --> 01:43:09.810
Bilodeau! Come.

1124
01:43:14.190 --> 01:43:15.940
Shut the door, please.

1125
01:43:20.360 --> 01:43:23.660
Éric, it's fucking millions!
We have to stop it.


1126
01:43:23.700 --> 01:43:25.110
Calm down. Sit.

1127
01:43:32.540 --> 01:43:36.580
You have to go to the RCMP,
not the Authority.


1128
01:43:38.840 --> 01:43:40.710
We're in contact with them.

1129
01:43:48.930 --> 01:43:52.520
What's happening here is madness.
I just found out.


1130
01:43:55.730 --> 01:43:58.770
Yes, Mr. Brunetta. 
It's Éric Asselin.

1131
01:43:58.820 --> 01:44:01.230
I have another colleague ready to talk.

1132
01:45:46.090 --> 01:45:47.940
You looking for someone?

1133
01:45:52.640 --> 01:45:55.930
Giguère isn't here today.
Apparently, he called in sick.


1134
01:45:56.520 --> 01:45:57.930
I don't know.

1135
01:45:59.850 --> 01:46:04.650
Listen, we got the loan agreement documents
from Dominion Investments.


1136
01:46:05.730 --> 01:46:07.860
Send them over. 
I'll take care of it.

1137
01:46:51.320 --> 01:46:52.990
This here…

1138
01:46:54.820 --> 01:46:56.490
is the 12th floor.

1139
01:46:59.200 --> 01:47:03.630
Bilodeau's office, 
Bernier's office…

1140
01:47:06.540 --> 01:47:08.300
and Vincent Lacroix's.

1141
01:47:10.130 --> 01:47:12.010
You need a code to get in.

1142
01:47:12.630 --> 01:47:16.350
There are a lot of files in there
you'd find very interesting.


1143
01:47:17.640 --> 01:47:20.520
I've rarely seen such a proactive witness.

1144
01:47:25.060 --> 01:47:27.480
I've held up my end of the deal.

1145
01:47:27.940 --> 01:47:30.990
Can I at least know
when you'll move in?


1146
01:47:31.030 --> 01:47:33.860
I'd rather not be around that day.

1147
01:47:37.030 --> 01:47:40.200
If I were you, I'd stay away
from the office later this week.


1148
01:47:47.170 --> 01:47:52.050
THURSDAY, AUGUST 25, 2005

1149
01:48:40.220 --> 01:48:41.430
Hold up your plate.

1150
01:48:46.600 --> 01:48:48.520
You'll make the next one.

1151
01:49:18.300 --> 01:49:21.100
Yeah. Thank you for coming.

1152
01:50:12.110 --> 01:50:15.860
RCMP! All employees,
please exit your offices immediately.


1153
01:50:15.900 --> 01:50:17.110
No one touch a thing!

1154
01:50:17.150 --> 01:50:18.320
RCMP?

1155
01:50:18.860 --> 01:50:22.700
Put down your document.

1156
01:50:24.830 --> 01:50:27.330
Sir, I'll ask you to
please put down that file.


1157
01:50:33.290 --> 01:50:35.750
Step away from your desk.

1158
01:51:01.820 --> 01:51:05.160
<i>Very bad news today
for thousands of small investors.</i>


1159
01:51:05.200 --> 01:51:09.000
<i>We all know how hard it is
to grow your savings for retirement.</i>


1160
01:51:09.040 --> 01:51:12.920
<i>A major fraud was uncovered
at Montreal company, Norbourg,</i>


1161
01:51:12.960 --> 01:51:15.290
<i>a large investment fund manager.</i>

1162
01:51:15.340 --> 01:51:19.590
<i>Yves, the company led by Vincent Lacroix
is alleged to have embezzled $70 million?</i>


1163
01:51:19.630 --> 01:51:20.670
<i>That's right.</i>

1164
01:51:20.720 --> 01:51:26.100
<i>The AMF, assisted by the RCMP
and provincial police,</i>


1165
01:51:26.140 --> 01:51:29.390
<i>investigated the notorious Vincent Lacroix.</i>

1166
01:51:58.040 --> 01:52:00.130
<i>…from December 31, 2004.</i>

1167
01:52:00.170 --> 01:52:04.180
<i>The company claimed to have $155 million,</i>

1168
01:52:04.220 --> 01:52:06.970
<i>when they in fact had $85.</i>

1169
01:52:07.010 --> 01:52:11.640
I have to present myself as another
fraud victim like the other investors.


1170
01:52:11.680 --> 01:52:14.690
<i>…false financial statements
for the past three years,</i>


1171
01:52:14.730 --> 01:52:17.690
<i>fabrication and falsification
of documents,</i>


1172
01:52:17.730 --> 01:52:21.610
<i>embezzlement,
at least 5,000 investors defrauded.</i>


1173
01:52:21.650 --> 01:52:24.740
<i>Pierre, it could be as high as 10,000.</i>

1174
01:52:24.780 --> 01:52:26.110
It's my only chance.

1175
01:52:27.030 --> 01:52:31.540
<i>Over 5,000 investors,
clients of Norbourg,</i>


1176
01:52:31.580 --> 01:52:35.580
<i>are wondering if they've
lost their entire investments.</i>


1177
01:52:35.620 --> 01:52:41.340
<i>The AMF is accusing the company
of embezzling $70 million</i>


1178
01:52:41.380 --> 01:52:44.300
<i>and has ordered them
to cease all activities.</i>


1179
01:52:44.340 --> 01:52:47.010
<i>Criminal charges may be filed…</i>

1180
01:53:17.500 --> 01:53:20.000
<i>After many long years before the courts,</i>

1181
01:53:20.040 --> 01:53:23.000
<i>after several attempted
class-action lawsuits,</i>


1182
01:53:23.050 --> 01:53:25.590
<i>the 9,200 investors swindled by Norbourg</i>

1183
01:53:25.630 --> 01:53:29.390
<i>failed to recover
their entire original investments.</i>


1184
01:53:29.430 --> 01:53:31.300
<i>Some were ruined.</i>

1185
01:54:32.700 --> 01:54:35.950
<i>Found guilty of fraud
on an unprecedented scale</i>


1186
01:54:35.990 --> 01:54:37.790
<i>in Quebec judicial history,</i>

1187
01:54:37.830 --> 01:54:42.960
<i>Vincent Lacroix still served
less than three years in prison.</i>


1188
01:55:04.020 --> 01:55:10.530
<i>He is now free and rebuilding his life.</i>

1189
01:55:12.280 --> 01:55:15.740
<i>As for Éric Asselin,
he did not stand trial</i>

1190
01:55:15.780 --> 01:55:19.950
<i>and was not convicted
in the Norbourg scandal.</i>


1191
01:55:20.000 --> 01:55:24.130
<i>He was, however,
found guilty of bankruptcy fraud in 2013.</i>


1192
01:59:21.740 --> 01:59:23.990
Translation by Elisabeth Gillies

1193
